node.text:
Grateful to KFYR for sharing our stories as patients who continue to battle infertility! We are 1 in 8. We will continue to speak our truths despite how incredibly vulnerable and difficult it is. There is a terrible stigma that surrounds infertility and no couple should suffer alone and in silence. 🍍 🌈 👶🏼 

This bill would have made the difference for North Dakota families with infertility disease who are unable to afford the cost that far exceeds $20,000. Children are the future and no family should be denied this dream because of a lack of medical coverage and insurance denials. 

We have a lot of educating to do before we bring back the bill next year. We will continue to pound the pavement, testify before committees, send emails, speak out, lobby, meet, and advocate for families in our state.

node.text: Today my school hosted our first ever St. Jude Trike-a-thon! 🚲 We had SO many kids come out to ride to support kids receiving cancer treatment at St. Jude hospital. ❤️ Our youngest learners (ages 3-7) raised $4,000+ and counting! 🤩 Thank you to the kids, their families and friends, @alphalitfargogf , and all of the volunteers that made this event so successful! 🎉 See you next year! #stjudetrikeathon #kidshelpingkids @stjude

node.text: I’m dreaming of international summer travel ... you too? ✈️ A couple of summer ago I went to London and Paris and took my dad with. 🗼 Our Finland trip was cancelled because of Covid, but we are planning a trip back to Finland next summer and Germany the following summer. My dad is fluent in German, but I’m not yet! Enter: @rosettastone . They are giving away 3 free months to any teacher or healthcare professional who wants to learn a new language! How cool is that? 🤩 Tag a friend in the comments who you’d love to travel with, and let me know which language you’d like to learn! 🌎 Link to sign up in profile. 🔗 #partner #ad

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Kayla Dornfeld on April 21, 2021 tagging @dandornfeld.

node.text:
24 months.

5 failed infertility treatments.

200+ shots and counting.

24 negative pregnancy tests.

50+ doctor appointments.

60+ ultrasounds.

10’s of thousands of dollars spent.

1000 tears falling on the bathroom floor.

Countless prayers answered of which we are forever grateful.

Dan and I are so excited to share that we are pregnant! Baby Bean is due on Christmas Day and we continue to praise God for this miracle and pray for a healthy full-term pregnancy. 

#wortheveryshot #niaw #ivfwarrior

node.text:
After 24 months on this fertility journey, we are so excited to share we had a successful transfer today with Baby Dornfeld! We will take a blood test on April 19 to confirm our little bean is safe and tucked in for the next 36 weeks. 

Wow. God did it. All of it. Through the lowest lows and highest highs. He did it. 

“Oh yes, you shaped me first inside, then out; you formed me in my mother’s womb. I thank you, High God—you’re breathtaking! Body and soul, I am marvelously made! I worship in adoration—what a creation! You know me inside and out, you know every bone in my body; You know exactly how I was made, bit by bit, how I was sculpted from nothing into something. Like an open book, you watched me grow from conception to birth; all the stages of my life were spread out before you, The days of my life all prepared before I’d even lived one day.”
‭‭Psalm‬ ‭139:13-16‬ 

We took lots of pictures because we never, ever want to forget a single moment of this magical day. #ivfwarrior

node.text:
You are loved more than you will ever know by someone who died to know you. 
Romans 5:8 💜

Happy Easter! A time to count our blessings and remember that all of our sins are forgiven. Every. Single. One. Jesus took the cross for you and me, and truth and life prevailed when he rose from the dead, just as he had promised he would do. 🙏🏼

node.text: Find a bestie who will gather your stepkids to blow confetti poppers on you when you wake up on your birthday. Find a bestie who will cry on the bathroom floor with you after negative pregnancy tests. Find a bestie who will ride with you on Target pick-ups just because. Find a bestie who prays without ceasing and without even asking her to. Find a bestie who will put your stepdaughter to bed at night. Find a bestie who will take you out to your favorite restaurant for your birthday dinner. Find a bestie who will unload your dishwasher just because. Find a bestie who makes you laugh so hard you cry and (almost) wet your pants. Find a bestie who will hold you during 100+ shots in your stomach. Find a bestie who loves you unconditionally. As I turn 36, I couldn’t be more grateful for God’s divine intervention. He placed @darikajean in my life just when I didn’t even know I needed her most. Find a bestie. 💓
